# Festag — no mobile auth container scroll

On **mobile** (≤768px), auth entry and auth chrome containers must **never** scroll.

## Surfaces

- `/enter` (Client / Developer chooser + video)
- `/login`, `/register` (`.al-root` / `.al-mobile-sheet` / `.al-sheet-body` / `.al-main`)
- Dev login / onboarding auth sheets that share the same mobile chrome

## Do

- Keep `overflow: hidden` (or `overflow-x: hidden; overflow-y: hidden`) on the mobile auth shell
- Fit content in the viewport with layout, spacing, and type scale — not scrolling
- If the keyboard covers a field, prefer layout/viewport fit — **do not** unlock page/sheet scroll

## Do not

- `overflow-y: auto` / `scroll` on `.al-main`, `.al-sheet-body`, `.al-mobile-sheet`, `.ae-root`, or equivalent auth shells on ≤768px
- `scrollIntoView` / touch-pan scrolling of the auth container to “fix” keyboard overlap
- Reintroduce scroll “just for short phones” — shorten UI instead

When touching mobile auth layout, verify the sheet cannot be dragged/scrolled by the user.
